# SkyTrack Data Warehouse - Analytics Layer Data Dictionary

This document describes the Analytics Layer views used for reporting and dashboarding in the SkyTrack Data Warehouse project. The purpose of these views is to provide business-friendly datasets for analytics, KPI tracking, and Power BI reporting.

---

# dim_passengers

**Purpose:** Stores passenger demographic information, contact details, travel history metrics, and loyalty segmentation used for customer analytics.

| Column Name    | Data Type | Description                                                                              |
| -------------- | --------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| passenger_id   | INT       | Unique identifier for each passenger.                                                    |
| first_name     | VARCHAR   | Passenger's first name.                                                                  |
| last_name      | VARCHAR   | Passenger's last name.                                                                   |
| gender         | VARCHAR   | Passenger's gender.                                                                      |
| date_of_birth  | DATE      | Passenger's date of birth.                                                               |
| nationality    | VARCHAR   | Passenger's nationality.                                                                 |
| loyalty_status | VARCHAR   | Loyalty tier assigned based on total tickets purchased (Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum). |
| email          | VARCHAR   | Passenger's email address.                                                               |
| phone_number   | VARCHAR   | Passenger's contact number.                                                              |
| total_tickets  | INT       | Total number of tickets purchased by the passenger.                                      |

---

# dim_employees

**Purpose:** Stores employee information used for workforce analysis, staffing insights, and employee segmentation based on years of service.

| Column Name     | Data Type | Description                                                               |
| --------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| employee_id     | INT       | Unique identifier for each employee.                                      |
| first_name      | VARCHAR   | Employee's first name.                                                    |
| last_name       | VARCHAR   | Employee's last name.                                                     |
| role            | VARCHAR   | Employee job role (Pilot, Cabin Crew, Ground Staff, etc.).                |
| base_airport_id | INT       | Airport where the employee is assigned.                                   |
| hire_date       | DATE      | Employee joining date.                                                    |
| email           | VARCHAR   | Employee email address.                                                   |
| employee_status | VARCHAR   | Employee tier based on years of service (Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum). |

---

# fact_booking

**Purpose:** Captures ticket booking transactions and booking behavior metrics. This view supports passenger analytics, booking trends, customer segmentation, and loyalty analysis.

| Column Name           | Data Type | Description                                                                          |
| --------------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| ticket_id             | INT       | Unique identifier for each ticket booking.                                           |
| passenger_id          | INT       | Passenger associated with the booking.                                               |
| flight_id             | INT       | Flight associated with the booking.                                                  |
| booking_date          | DATE      | Date on which the booking was made.                                                  |
| class                 | VARCHAR   | Travel class selected by the passenger (Economy, Premium Economy, Business, First).  |
| price_usd             | DECIMAL   | Ticket price in USD.                                                                 |
| booking_segment       | VARCHAR   | Customer spending category (Budget, Standard, Premium).                              |
| loyalty_points_earned | DECIMAL   | Loyalty points awarded based on ticket class and ticket value.                       |
| booking_lead_days     | INT       | Number of days between booking date and flight departure date.                       |
| booking_type          | VARCHAR   | Booking category based on lead time (Advance Booking, Regular Booking, Last Minute). |

---

# fact_flight

**Purpose:** Provides operational flight information and performance metrics used for monitoring airline operations, flight utilization, and route analysis.

| Column Name            | Data Type | Description                                                             |
| ---------------------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| flight_id              | INT       | Unique identifier for each flight.                                      |
| flight_no              | VARCHAR   | Flight number assigned to the flight.                                   |
| airline_code           | VARCHAR   | Airline operating the flight.                                           |
| origin_airport_id      | INT       | Identifier of the departure airport.                                    |
| origin_airport         | VARCHAR   | Name of the departure airport.                                          |
| origin_country         | VARCHAR   | Country of the departure airport.                                       |
| destination_airport_id | INT       | Identifier of the arrival airport.                                      |
| destination_airport    | VARCHAR   | Name of the arrival airport.                                            |
| destination_country    | VARCHAR   | Country of the arrival airport.                                         |
| departure_time         | DATETIME  | Scheduled flight departure time.                                        |
| arrival_time           | DATETIME  | Scheduled flight arrival time.                                          |
| aircraft_type          | VARCHAR   | Aircraft model used for the flight.                                     |
| status                 | VARCHAR   | Operational status of the flight (Completed, Delayed, Cancelled).       |
| flight_duration_hours  | DECIMAL   | Total flight duration in hours.                                         |
| status_category        | VARCHAR   | Categorized flight status used for operational reporting.               |
| flight_type            | VARCHAR   | Flight category based on duration (Short Haul, Medium Haul, Long Haul). |

---

# fact_route_performance

**Purpose:** Provides aggregated route-level performance metrics used to evaluate route profitability, customer demand, and operational efficiency.

| Column Name               | Data Type | Description                                                          |
| ------------------------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| origin_airport_id         | INT       | Identifier of the departure airport.                                 |
| origin_airport            | VARCHAR   | Name of the departure airport.                                       |
| origin_country            | VARCHAR   | Country of the departure airport.                                    |
| destination_airport_id    | INT       | Identifier of the arrival airport.                                   |
| destination_airport       | VARCHAR   | Name of the arrival airport.                                         |
| destination_country       | VARCHAR   | Country of the arrival airport.                                      |
| total_flights             | INT       | Total number of flights operated on the route.                       |
| total_bookings            | INT       | Total number of bookings made for the route.                         |
| total_revenue             | DECIMAL   | Total revenue generated from bookings on the route.                  |
| avg_ticket_price          | DECIMAL   | Average ticket price for the route.                                  |
| avg_flight_duration_hours | DECIMAL   | Average flight duration for the route in hours.                      |
| route_type                | VARCHAR   | Route classification based on countries (Domestic or International). |

